ENTRY       EC 1.5.1.39                 Enzyme
NAME        FMN reductase [NAD(P)H];
            FRG
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on the CH-NH group of donors;
            With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
SYSNAME     FMNH2:NAD(P)+ oxidoreductase
REACTION    FMNH2 + NAD(P)+ = FMN + NAD(P)H + H+ [RN:R05705 R05706]
ALL_REAC    R05705 R05706
SUBSTRATE   FMNH2 [CPD:C01847];
            NAD+ [CPD:C00003];
            NADP+ [CPD:C00006]
PRODUCT     FMN [CPD:C00061];
            NADH [CPD:C00004];
            NADPH [CPD:C00005];
            H+ [CPD:C00080]
COMMENT     Contains FMN. The enzyme can utilize NADH and NADPH with similar reaction rates. Different from EC 1.5.1.42, FMN reductase (NADH) and EC 1.5.1.38, FMN reductase (NADPH). The luminescent bacterium Vibrio harveyi possesses all three enzymes [1]. Also reduces riboflavin and FAD, but more slowly.
HISTORY     EC 1.5.1.39 created 2011
